headline: Deere Startup Collaborator Cohort Puts Technology At Heart Of Growth Story
summary: Deere (NYSE:DE) has selected five companies for its 2026 Startup Collaborator Program. The program focuses on technology partnerships across agriculture, construction, and roadbuilding. The announcement highlights Deere's efforts to advance precision agriculture and autonomous systems. For investors watching Deere at a share price of $598.11, the company is pairing its established equipment business with ongoing work alongside younger technology firms.
